            <p>A $5,000 surgery with an 80% reimbursement rate and $250 deductible works out to: <strong>($5,000 - $250) × 0.80 = $3,800 reimbursed</strong>. You'd pay $1,200 out-of-pocket instead of $5,000. That's pet insurance doing its job.</p>
